Definition.WordDefinition: Uncanny \Un*can"ny\, a. Not canny; unsafe; strange; weird; ghostly. --Sir W. Scott. -- {Un*can"ni*ness}, n. --G. Eliot. [1913 Webster]

uncanny adj 1: suggesting the operation of supernatural influences; "an eldritch screech"; "the three weird sisters"; "stumps...had uncanny shapes as of monstrous creatures"- John Galsworthy; "an unearthly light"; "he could hear the unearthly scream of some curlew piercing the din"- Henry Kingsley [syn: {eldritch}, {weird}, {unearthly}] 2: beyond what is natural; "his uncanny sense of direction"; (`unco' is chiefly Scottish) [syn: {unco}]
